HEADWORD: Introrse
<hw>In*trorse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>introrsus</ets> inward, contr. from <ets>introversus</ets>. See
<er>Introvert</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Turning or facing
inward, or toward the axis of the part to which it belongs.</def>
